In Yield App v3 there will be several improvements related to interface, potentially including total earnings but we will be able to see details as soon as it will be revealed by our team.

However, there is something you can still do now to track your total earnings:

1) Open mobile app and if you kept relatively similar number of assets for extended period of time, you can calculate your earnings based on 30d earnings shown on dashboard. When you click on small symbol next to 30d, you will be able to see earnings for each asset.
2) Go to Transactions then Earnings/Staking ledgers and using filters, check detailed earnings for each month and for every asset.

I know it’s not perfect but that’s the best workaround for now! 🙏

text:
I won't even try to predict the price of the token, but as far as the projects (and not tokens) are concerned, as a 2+ years user, I am very much bullish about Yield App and Haven1.

I've been accumulating YLD tokens since it was announced that the rewards from staked YLD will be paid in esH1. For me, the risk of losing from buying YLD is lower than the potential gains from H1 and/or YLD. Best case scenario is that

YLD and H1 will gain in value. And I'm talking about 5 years perspective here (when all my current YLDs will be "converted" to H1).

Therefore, "potential token dump" is not a concern for me. Actually, if the price goes down even more, I'll accumulate even more YLD, to get even more H1 in the future.

Nobody knows if any dump will actually happen, but in the past there were at least a couple of times where there were a lot of FUD about "potential token dump", and that never materialized. Majority of people have their YLDs locked inside the platform. Of course, the 12% rate on YLD is a nice incentive to keep the token, but it's not that the incentive will be completely gone after 1/1/24. I believe there are more people like me who believe in the team and both projects and will keep their YLDs to earn H1. Or to stay on Diamond level.

Therefore, I doubt that there will be a massive token dump after 1/1/24.
